n h ovn party, i- entirely vvi-e\nin refusing to follow where he points\nthe way H< is \u201ccult iv aled in -p it\nLike Canning's boy 'talesman, he\nrotted before It\u2019 ripened. With all lus\neloquence, hi- geniality, his generosity,\nhis courage, his tenacity, Bryan hi\nnever been a safe leader because lie\nha* never been a- >nnd statesman\nHis theories have t often been mere\nvagaries. With much that was good in\ntheir origination there has been too\nmuch that was bad and dangerous ip\ntheir development. The stable ele\nments of the Republic have natural)\u2019\nshied at such leadership. And yet this\nman'* personal following is enormous\nand the Democratic party must reckon\ntherewith. It is a case of \"he damned\nif I do, or l;e damned if I don\u2019t.\u201d To\nnominate him again certainly spells\ndefeat. Not to nominate him means\u2014\nwell, what don't it mean to alienate the\ngreat mass of Bryanite adorers? Al\ntogether. it looks as if the Democratic\nparty were between \"the devil and the\ndeep sea.\u201d on the eve of another Na\ntional election.\nBUSINESS PROSPECTS\nBRIGHTEN\nTHINGS are looking up very de\ncidedly in the industrial world.\nFor several weeks there has\nbeen improvement all along the line in\nthe general business situation. Mills\nhave been resuming: the railroads arc\nusing more of their cars, and fewer\n|>Ople are out of work The larger\nfinancial circles arc showing their be\nlief in the passage of the storm A\nnotable evidence is the Pennsylvania\u2019s\nmarked success in placing $40,000,000\n4 per cent, bonds at qfi Clearing\nhouses report a decided increase in\ncash. Crop reports arc highly favor\nable. So that the business outlook has\nsolid facts on which to build a good\nhope, and conditions everywhere jus\ntify a reasonable optimism. Nobody\nis looking for a boom or any tidal\nwave of prosperity Indeed, it is to\nhe hoped that nothing of that sort may\ncome to pass What is wanted at this\nlime in these United States, is a steady\nami solid increase in industry and\ntrade, on a safe and healthy basis\u2014and\nthat is what the near future seems to\npromise Wherefore, let u> thank God\nand lake courage.\nWrath And A Record\nHavre dc Grace has been in the\nthroes of a hot controversy over the\nbill 01 the late Legislature, making it\nmandatory upon the City Council ui\nthat town to levy s,iou annually for the\npanic- that have lormed a company to\nlake, over the old P., B. W. K. K.\nbridge and convert it (ostensibly j into\na highway bridge The impression pre\nvails among many of the people that\nit was one of those \"-kin games\" be\ntween the Kailr ad Company and the\npolitical bosses, wherein \"the dear\npeople get left every time.\" and some\ni them have been {laying their vit\nriolic respect* to the \"leader*\" of the\nLegislature, particularly 1 the Hon.\nMurray indiver el al Whereupon\nm M II I-alley, lanuli.iriy known a\n\"Mike.\" rushes t the defense of said\n\"leader-\" in a public letter, that bris\ntles with fury epithet- Evidently,\nln>wever. Michael'* wrath undid his\njudgment, and without reckoning on\nhi- fact- In lind off tin- unfortunate\n-onteiiei I would suggest that the\nLd tor toi the Havre de Grace Re\npul.lli an I ml lu friends look up Mr\nManta S I'oul-oii s past while he re\n-1 in North East. Cecil c uinty. etc,\netc\" I which diry intimation of an\nnnav.ll r. v rd n former days Mr.\nI\u2019ollls .11 Iters the i d\u2019ow ng delicious\nrep am r\nTo the Editor 1 tin Item crane Led\nger\nI>e ir Sir 1 understand that M H.\nLain y suggests that some one look nji\nmy record while a re.idem of North\nEast Hen it I.\nI win horn al North East. Cecil\ncounty. Maryland, and lived the first\ntwo yi .tr. .a my life ill that I wen If\nreport, are true, these two years were\ntunes of greal activity ..11 my part, and\ny .nr friend Fahey has evidently proof\nthat I br .lsi t rattle .r cried at night\nSincerely voiir..\nM S' lULSO.N\nI\u2019nnctpio Furnace, Md \\pr 15, Kg S.\nMr \\